jt-pve-storage-netapp (0.1.6-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Full Clone Support Release
  * New Feature: Full Clone from VM Snapshot
    - Clone a VM from any specific snapshot to create independent VM
    - Uses temporary FlexClone for snapshot data access
    - Automatic cleanup of temporary FlexClones (1 hour expiry)
    - Works with both iSCSI and FC protocols
  * New Feature: Full Clone from Current State
    - Full Clone of running or stopped VMs
    - PVE/qemu-img reads directly from current volume
  * Technical Implementation:
    - path() creates temporary FlexClone when snapshot access needed
    - Temporary FlexClone LUN automatically mapped to igroup
    - State tracking in /var/run/pve-storage-netapp-temp-clones.json
    - Cleanup runs automatically during storage status checks
  * New API Methods:
    - volume_is_splitting(): Check if clone split is in progress
    - volume_wait_clone_split(): Wait for clone split to complete
  * Linked Clone Improvement:
    - Linked Clone from template now stays space-efficient (no auto-split)
  * Storage Deactivation:
    - deactivate_storage now properly cleans up iSCSI sessions
    - Flushes device buffers and removes multipath devices
    - Logs out from iSCSI targets when storage is disabled/removed
    - Safety check: skips cleanup for devices still in use
  * Bug Fixes:
    - Fixed list_images incorrectly showing FlexClones as templates
    - Fixed igroup name lookup in temp FlexClone creation
    - Fixed wait_for_multipath_device parameter format
    - Added retry logic for stale has_flexclone metadata during template deletion
  * Documentation Updates:
    - Updated installation SOP with multipath.conf configuration
    - Added security documentation (password storage, API permissions)
    - Added ONTAP account setup options (Cluster vs SVM level)

 -- Jason Cheng (Jason Tools) <jason@jason.tools>  Fri, 24 Jan 2026 19:21:00 +0800

jt-pve-storage-netapp (0.1.5-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Template Support Release
  * New Feature: Full Template Support
    - Implemented create_base method for VM-to-template conversion
    - Implemented rename_volume method for volume renaming
    - Added find_free_diskname helper for disk allocation
    - Uses __pve_base__ snapshot as template marker
  * Fixed: "storage definition has no path" error on template creation
    - Plugin now handles block storage template creation natively
    - No longer falls back to file-based create_base implementation
  * Fixed: list_images now correctly identifies template volumes
    - Template volumes return base-XXX-disk-X instead of vm-XXX-disk-X
    - Detection based on presence of __pve_base__ snapshot
  * Fixed: path() now handles missing LUNs gracefully
    - Returns synthetic path when LUN doesn't exist (orphaned volume)
    - Allows deletion of orphaned volumes via PVE UI
  * Added API.pm volume_rename method for ONTAP volume renaming

 -- Jason Cheng (Jason Tools) <jason@jason.tools>  Fri, 03 Jan 2025 22:00:00 +0000

jt-pve-storage-netapp (0.1.4-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * FC SAN Support Release
  * New Feature: Fibre Channel (FC) SAN Protocol Support
    - New configuration option: ontap-protocol (iscsi|fc)
    - Automatic FC HBA WWPN discovery from /sys/class/fc_host
    - FC igroup creation with 'fcp' protocol
    - Support for multiple FC HBA ports per node
    - FC LIP (Loop Initialization Primitive) for LUN rescan
  * New Module: FC.pm
    - get_fc_wwpns(): Get all FC HBA port WWPNs
    - is_fc_available(): Check if FC HBA exists
    - rescan_fc_hosts(): Trigger FC and SCSI rescan
    - format_wwn(): Convert WWN to standard format
  * Robustness Improvements:
    - Concurrent disk allocation now retries with next available ID
    - Aggregate validation on storage activation
    - Configurable device discovery timeout (ontap-device-timeout)
    - Improved error messages with actionable hints
  * Performance Improvements:
    - Batch LUN query in list_images (reduces API calls significantly)
  * Bug Fixes:
    - Fixed path() and snapshot_rollback to support FC protocol
    - Fixed protocol-aware device rescanning throughout codebase
    - Fixed async job handling for DELETE and PATCH API calls
    - Volume deletion now properly waits for ONTAP job completion
    - Fixed template (base-xxx-disk-x) volume name handling
    - parse_volname now correctly returns isBase flag for templates
  * Compatibility:
    - FC and iSCSI use same multipath configuration
    - FC and iSCSI use same WWID-based device identification
    - Existing iSCSI configurations continue to work (default protocol)
  * Documentation:
    - Added FC SAN configuration examples
    - Updated CONFIGURATION.md with ontap-protocol option

 -- Jason Cheng (Jason Tools) <jason@jason.tools>  Fri, 03 Jan 2025 12:00:00 +0000

jt-pve-storage-netapp (0.1.3-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * FlexClone Support Release
  * New Feature: Linked Clone via NetApp FlexClone
    - Template and linked clone now supported
    - Instant clone creation (no data copy needed)
    - Space-efficient: clones share unchanged blocks with parent
    - Automatic LUN identity for cloned volumes
    - FlexClone license check with helpful error message
  * Safety Improvements:
    - Prevent deletion of templates with clone children
    - Clear error message listing dependent clones
  * Bug Fixes:
    - Fixed path() method causing system hangs when device not accessible
    - path() now returns synthetic path when device not found locally
    - Allows deletion of VMs whose devices were never activated
    - Prevents kernel hung tasks caused by faulty multipath devices
  * Package Installation Improvements:
    - Fixed prerm script hanging during upgrade (added 5s timeout for pvesm)
    - Fixed postinst script potential hang (added timeout for systemctl calls)
    - All deb maintainer scripts now have proper timeout protection
  * Volume Sizing:
    - Enabled volume autogrow (expands automatically when needed)
    - Reduced initial overhead to 64MB
    - Volume max size set to 2x LUN size

 -- Jason Cheng (Jason Tools) <jason@jason.tools>  Fri, 03 Jan 2025 00:15:00 +0000

jt-pve-storage-netapp (0.1.2-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Bug Fix & Dependency Release
  * Critical Bug Fix:
    - Enabled volume autogrow: volume automatically expands when needed
    - Reduced initial overhead to 64MB (was 5GB)
    - Volume max size set to 2x LUN size for safety
  * Added missing dependency:
    - psmisc: provides 'fuser' command for device-in-use detection
      (required by is_device_in_use() function in Multipath.pm)
  * Documentation updates:
    - Added psmisc to installation instructions
    - Added lsscsi to recommended packages for troubleshooting

